headlines.description: — Jalen Duren had a career-high 23 rebounds along with 24 points and five assists as the Detroit Pistons won three of four games for the first time in nearly two years, beating the Toronto Raptors 113-104 on Wednesday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Duren has career-high 23 rebounds as Pistons beat Raptors 113-104 for 3rd win in 4

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero handled the finesse part and let his Orlando teammates handle the physicality.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero scores 21, leads Magic over Nets 114-106

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 46 points, including the go-ahead 3-pointer in overtime, to help the Chicago Bulls outlast the Indiana Pacers 132-129 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan's 46 leads Bulls past Pacers in OT

headlines.description: — After four months of looking up at others in the Western Conference, Denver finally is alone atop the standings.
headlines.shortLinkText: Denver beats Miami 100-88 in an NBA Finals rematch and moves atop the Western Conference

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges scored 27 points, rookie Vasa Micic added a career-best 25 and the Charlotte Hornets defeated the Memphis Grizzlies 110-98 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miles Bridges scores 27, rookie Vasa Micic has career-best 25 as Hornets beat Grizzlies 110-98

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell returned from a seven-game absence and the Cleveland Cavaliers stemmed a two-game slide with style and on the road against an opponent that...
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell returns and the Cavaliers hit 20 3s in a 116-95 win over the Pelicans

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic's triple-double streak is over as the focus turns to his tender left hamstring.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 21, triple-double streak ends at 7 as Mavs slog past Warriors 109-99

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 36 points and the Portland Trail Blazers held off the Atlanta Hawks for a 106-102 victory on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons has 36 and Ayton has 33 in Portland's 106-102 win over the Hawks

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 17 points, 19 rebounds and 10 assists, and the Sacramento Kings beat the Los Angeles Lakers 120-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis has triple-double as Kings beat Lakers 120-107 for 4-game season sweep
